WEBVTT

00:20.178 --> 00:23.178
♪ Feel I'm going back ♪

00:23.178 --> 00:26.178
♪ To Massachusetts ♪

00:29.178 --> 00:32.553
♪ Something's telling me ♪

00:32.553 --> 00:35.887
♪ I must go home ♪

00:37.387 --> 00:39.178
[Jackie] These motherfuckers
weren't doing anything

00:39.178 --> 00:40.679
the rest of us weren't doing.

00:40.679 --> 00:42.804
Jackie, they got
the wrong guy.

00:42.804 --> 00:44.762
Chuck Stuart
blew out his own guts

00:44.762 --> 00:46.303
to get away
with killing his wife...

00:48.887 --> 00:50.512
and said some nigger did it.

00:50.512 --> 00:52.720
I mean, I believe him too,
he told me a black guy did it.

00:52.720 --> 00:54.387
Would you shit in a fucking bag
for the rest of your life

00:54.387 --> 00:55.512
to get away
with killing your wife?

00:55.512 --> 00:57.095
I love my wife.

00:57.095 --> 00:58.762
I love my wife too,

00:58.762 --> 01:01.220
but I'm a big fan
of keeping things simple.

01:01.220 --> 01:03.804
Look, I got no love lost for
the Boston Police Department,

01:03.804 --> 01:05.470
but this fucking commission
that they set up

01:05.470 --> 01:06.970
to investigate
this Charles Stuart shit,

01:06.970 --> 01:08.679
the St. Clair Commission,
letting it leak

01:08.679 --> 01:10.595
that they wanted
jail time for cops.

01:10.595 --> 01:14.387
Fuck that. U.S. attorney
is losing his mind.

01:14.387 --> 01:16.845
[Salvie] Speaking of,
I cannot believe I'm in a line

01:16.845 --> 01:18.720
for this miserable fuck.

01:18.720 --> 01:20.720
Matthew Cook was an asshole.

01:20.720 --> 01:22.762
Salvie, for Christ's sake.

01:22.762 --> 01:24.387
Show some fucking respect.

01:26.553 --> 01:27.512
[Josie]
Jackie.

01:30.637 --> 01:32.512
I didn't think
anybody'd come.

01:32.512 --> 01:34.261
I knew you loved him, but

01:34.261 --> 01:36.136
I didn't think
anybody else would come.

01:36.136 --> 01:37.929
Josie, your husband...

01:39.553 --> 01:43.095
he was-- he was like
Jack Kennedy.

01:43.095 --> 01:44.804
No one knew
what they had.

01:45.804 --> 01:48.136
Yes. Thanks.

01:48.136 --> 01:51.220
You know, I got this
Grassy Knoll theory

01:51.220 --> 01:54.261
about the night that this whole
fucking city went to shit.

01:54.261 --> 01:58.470
It was the time that Mayor Flynn
sent the cops on the ice.

01:58.470 --> 02:00.261
You remember that?
Bruins/Canadiens?

02:00.261 --> 02:03.929
The fucking fight went
all the way up in the stands.

02:03.929 --> 02:06.095
What used to make
this city great

02:06.095 --> 02:08.804
was that it was run
by bad men

02:08.804 --> 02:11.387
who understood
that they were bad.

02:11.387 --> 02:15.136
And then some stupid fuck goes
on the TV and tells everybody,

02:15.136 --> 02:17.428
"You can't act like this
anymore,

02:17.428 --> 02:19.470
not even in a Bruins game."

02:19.470 --> 02:20.512
[sniffs]

02:20.512 --> 02:22.428
And now...

02:22.428 --> 02:24.679
can't even call a guy
a faggot, he deserves it.

02:24.679 --> 02:27.011
I don't-- it's-- I--

02:28.970 --> 02:30.804
So, what you're saying is,

02:30.804 --> 02:34.428
you're upset 'cause this is
a civil place to live now.

02:34.428 --> 02:37.512
What the fuck we been working
for the last 20 years?

02:37.512 --> 02:39.261
Well, I always
just thought the FBI

02:39.261 --> 02:42.011
wanted to be the baddest
motherfucker around.

02:43.804 --> 02:45.720
Look, I'm only gonna
say this once,

02:45.720 --> 02:46.804
'cause you're my friend.

02:46.804 --> 02:48.303
Take it how you will.

02:49.220 --> 02:51.011
You're fucking your life up.

02:51.011 --> 02:52.762
What are you
talking about?

02:52.762 --> 02:54.553
This shit
you're talking about.

02:54.553 --> 02:56.512
What we used to
get away with?

02:56.512 --> 02:59.553
Times are changing.
It's not 1983 anymore.

02:59.553 --> 03:01.595
You got to knock it off, pal.

03:01.595 --> 03:02.887
What's the matter
with you?

03:02.887 --> 03:04.637
Look at me.

03:04.637 --> 03:06.845
I love my job.

03:06.845 --> 03:09.220
Now my kids can't stand me.

03:09.220 --> 03:11.261
I got nothin'.

03:11.261 --> 03:13.512
Same thing's gonna happen
to you, Jackie.

03:13.512 --> 03:15.303
What, did your wife finally
smarten up and leave you?

03:15.303 --> 03:17.345
Is that what
this is all about?

03:17.345 --> 03:18.845
-[laughs]
-You stupid fuck.

03:18.845 --> 03:21.261
You're never gonna learn.

03:21.261 --> 03:22.887
What? Come on.

03:22.887 --> 03:24.887
You can't take a joke?
Salvie, come on.

03:24.887 --> 03:27.595
Hey, where you goin'?
Salvie, come on.

03:27.595 --> 03:29.095
Hey.

03:29.095 --> 03:30.720
Whoa. Fuck.

03:30.720 --> 03:31.970
Hey, Rohr!

03:31.970 --> 03:34.762
You said you'd give us $50

03:34.762 --> 03:37.387
to show up and make a crowd
for the widow.

03:37.387 --> 03:39.136
[sniffles and coughs]

03:46.428 --> 03:48.720
Are you fuckin' kiddin'?
There's only 20 here!

03:48.720 --> 03:52.011
You forget what state
you're living in, pal?

03:52.011 --> 03:54.428
This is Massachusetts.

03:54.428 --> 03:57.011
Tax is a bitch.

03:57.011 --> 03:59.095
Thanks for nothin', Rohr.

03:59.095 --> 04:02.053
I don't know how the Globe
found out, but there it is.

04:02.053 --> 04:03.887
Members of
the St. Clair Commission,

04:03.887 --> 04:05.720
wanted jail time
for Boston police.

04:05.720 --> 04:09.303
Now, who do you think
they're talkin' 'bout?

04:09.303 --> 04:10.637
You.

04:10.637 --> 04:12.053
And you think
that's a good thing?

04:12.053 --> 04:13.387
I pushed jail time for cops.

04:13.387 --> 04:16.512
The U.S. attorney,
unfortunately, didn't agree.

04:16.512 --> 04:19.387
Now, why else would I leave
the U.S. Attorney's office,

04:19.387 --> 04:21.261
come work for the county DA,
if this wasn't the kind of work

04:21.261 --> 04:23.303
that I wanted to get done?

04:23.303 --> 04:24.970
Cops aren't fans
of the Globe,  and

04:24.970 --> 04:27.011
cops make cases
for the district attorney.

04:27.011 --> 04:28.804
So let me ask you this again.

04:28.804 --> 04:32.637
You think it's a good thing
that your heroics got mentioned?

04:32.637 --> 04:33.387
Hmm.

04:35.136 --> 04:36.387
Hey, come on.

04:39.136 --> 04:40.929
Come on, DeCourcy.

04:51.261 --> 04:53.887
[sighs and clears throat]

05:00.303 --> 05:01.303
Excuse me.

05:07.136 --> 05:09.428
Their coffee's on me.
Keep the change.

05:12.303 --> 05:14.470
Hey, thank you
for your service.

05:15.970 --> 05:18.136
You just couldn't
make it easy, huh?

05:18.136 --> 05:20.136
Who learns that way?

06:07.220 --> 06:08.512
[typewriter clacking]

06:08.512 --> 06:09.887
♪ rap music plays ♪

06:15.595 --> 06:16.845
♪ You down with OPP ♪

06:16.845 --> 06:18.136
♪ Yeah, you know me ♪

06:18.136 --> 06:19.387
♪ You down with OPP ♪

06:19.387 --> 06:20.553
♪ Yeah, you know me ♪

06:20.553 --> 06:21.804
♪ You down with OPP ♪

06:21.804 --> 06:23.011
♪  Yeah, you know me ♪

06:23.011 --> 06:24.303
♪ Who's down with OPP? ♪

06:24.303 --> 06:26.053
-Here's the warrant.
-Hold on to it.

06:26.053 --> 06:29.053
Hey, listen up, assholes.
I'm only going to say this once.

06:29.053 --> 06:33.303
This is a racially charged
situation. It's very delicate.

06:33.303 --> 06:34.720
Your strength
is the spirit of the law.

06:34.720 --> 06:35.845
[laughs]

06:35.845 --> 06:36.929
Let's go.

06:40.345 --> 06:42.887
-♪ You down with OPP ♪
-♪ Yeah, you know me ♪

06:42.887 --> 06:45.303
-♪  You down with OPP ♪
-[door crashes]

06:45.303 --> 06:46.887
[officer] Boston police!
Show me your hands!

06:46.887 --> 06:48.387
Don't move! Don't move!

06:48.387 --> 06:50.095
-Come on!
-Get 'em up!

06:50.095 --> 06:51.428
[Ren and Stimpy episode
plays on television]

06:51.428 --> 06:53.261
What the fuck, Stevie?

06:53.261 --> 06:54.345
These aren't the guys.

06:56.512 --> 06:59.053
[all shouting]

06:59.053 --> 07:00.553
[officer]
He's goin' out the window!

07:00.553 --> 07:01.720
Get him!

07:01.720 --> 07:03.095
Get it open!
He's out the window!

07:04.762 --> 07:06.887
Ah, shit!

07:06.887 --> 07:08.053
Fuck!

07:08.053 --> 07:09.387
[Steve groaning]

07:09.387 --> 07:11.303
Thought you read the fucking
warrant, Stevie!

07:11.303 --> 07:13.470
-I did!
-Give me that warrant!

07:17.303 --> 07:19.804
-What's that door say?
-[Stevie] 217.

07:19.804 --> 07:21.470
That's the wrong
fucking door!

07:21.470 --> 07:23.428
-How the fuck did that happen?
-Oh, I know.

07:23.428 --> 07:24.970
Your mother smoked
too many Kools

07:24.970 --> 07:27.136
she was pregnant with you,
you dyslexic motherfucker.

07:29.553 --> 07:31.470
Come out of there or I'll pull
the fucking short hairs

07:31.470 --> 07:33.011
off the back of your neck
one by one.

07:33.011 --> 07:34.553
[Roach]
Show me your fucking warrant.

07:34.553 --> 07:36.929
Oh, yeah, I got your fucking
warrant right here.

07:38.303 --> 07:39.845
[overlapping chatter]

07:39.845 --> 07:41.762
Chief. Hey, Chief. Hey!

07:41.762 --> 07:44.178
Chief, Chief.

07:44.178 --> 07:47.220
Hey, is there a reason my first
case back in Superior Court

07:47.220 --> 07:49.053
is a case out of Bromley Heath?

07:49.053 --> 07:51.178
Ward, are you an asshole?

07:51.178 --> 07:52.845
A cop gets shot.

07:52.845 --> 07:54.595
This is as close
to a slam-dunk conviction

07:54.595 --> 07:55.762
as you're gonna get.

07:57.053 --> 07:58.679
What the fuck
you so upset about?

07:58.679 --> 08:00.679
Look, Chief, there's
a reputation you get, right?

08:00.679 --> 08:02.428
Black lawyer working
guns and drugs--

08:02.428 --> 08:04.845
Look, y-you're
overthinking this.

08:04.845 --> 08:07.845
I put you on this because you're
gonna put the shit-bum away.

08:07.845 --> 08:10.428
And you might make things easier
between you and the BPD.

08:10.428 --> 08:13.011
I don't know anything
that'd do that.

08:13.011 --> 08:14.595
Better not fuck it up.

08:29.679 --> 08:31.762
[rock music playing]

08:39.512 --> 08:41.887
Let's go, guys. Out.
Everybody out.

08:41.887 --> 08:43.345
Let's go.
Closing time.

08:43.345 --> 08:44.762
[man]
Come on, Hook!

08:44.762 --> 08:46.637
-Let's go!
-Lemme finish my beer.

08:46.637 --> 08:51.720
[annoyed chatter]

09:07.637 --> 09:09.387
-What's up, Bill?
-What's happenin'?

09:09.387 --> 09:11.220
-How you doin', guys?
-How you doin'?

09:28.053 --> 09:31.679
Holy shit, those look like
fucking Army guns to me.

09:31.679 --> 09:33.470
-You said you needed 'em quick.
-[man] Yeah.

09:33.470 --> 09:35.136
But not so as
to get a life sentence

09:35.136 --> 09:36.762
carrying a fucking M16.

09:36.762 --> 09:38.136
They shoot where they point?

09:38.136 --> 09:39.595
I'd assume so.

09:39.595 --> 09:41.929
Then they're fine.

09:41.929 --> 09:46.136
Where did you get your hands
on an AK-47?

09:46.136 --> 09:48.387
Brother brought 'em
back from 'Nam.

09:48.387 --> 09:49.387
Killed three gooks
to get them.

09:54.470 --> 09:55.970
[officer] What do you know
about that color?

09:57.178 --> 09:58.845
Barry, you all right?

09:58.845 --> 10:00.095
[knocks]

10:00.095 --> 10:01.178
[door lock buzzes]

10:01.178 --> 10:02.637
No way...

10:05.387 --> 10:08.095
What the fuck are you doing
in Bromley Heath?

10:08.095 --> 10:10.804
-Fuck you think I was doing?
-I think you were getting high.

10:10.804 --> 10:13.470
No, look, Jackie,
this ain't my fault.

10:13.470 --> 10:15.011
Don't talk like I'm your mother.

10:15.011 --> 10:16.929
You think you're my only snitch?

10:16.929 --> 10:19.845
-Narcs kicked in the wrong door.
-You shouldn't have been there!

10:19.845 --> 10:22.762
[chair clatters]

10:22.762 --> 10:25.637
Look, I got a guy, a lead.

10:25.637 --> 10:27.845
Goes right to Prince Street.
The office.

10:27.845 --> 10:29.970
This guy gives you
Frank Salemme.

10:29.970 --> 10:31.261
And?

10:31.261 --> 10:33.220
And what?

10:33.220 --> 10:34.804
You want to hear more?

10:34.804 --> 10:36.303
Get me the fuck out of here.

10:40.845 --> 10:42.762
So, what, you,
you gonna get me out?

10:46.720 --> 10:48.637
I'll figure something out.

10:48.637 --> 10:50.845
[Roach] You know,
you're a good shit, Jackie.

10:50.845 --> 10:52.804
Don't know why they say
you're a prick.

10:52.804 --> 10:54.929
It's a rumor
my wife started.

10:59.261 --> 11:00.845
Hey. Hey, counselor.

11:00.845 --> 11:02.470
Hey, Jackie, what's goin' on?

11:02.470 --> 11:03.845
The cop shooting?
Bromley Heath?

11:03.845 --> 11:06.220
Yeah, I gave it
to the new guy, Ward. Why?

11:06.220 --> 11:08.095
Friend of mine asked me
to take a look.

11:08.095 --> 11:10.220
Oh, you're gonna love
DeCourcy Ward.

11:10.220 --> 11:11.512
Why is that?

11:11.512 --> 11:12.887
Affirmative action hire.

11:12.887 --> 11:15.011
Oh, Christ. How bad?

11:15.011 --> 11:17.178
He was on
the St. Clair Commission.

11:17.178 --> 11:18.845
[laughs]

11:21.053 --> 11:22.011
Fuck me.

12:04.804 --> 12:06.387
[engine revving]

12:06.387 --> 12:07.762
[tires screech]

12:10.345 --> 12:11.428
Move! Move!

12:11.428 --> 12:13.345
I see it, the bag!

12:13.345 --> 12:14.261
[men shouting indistinctly]

12:14.261 --> 12:15.887
Bag down, bag down!

12:16.929 --> 12:18.512
[Jackie]
Fellas.

12:18.512 --> 12:20.136
-There he is.
-And here comes trouble.

12:20.136 --> 12:24.095
Darling, when you gonna get rid
of that husband of yours?

12:24.095 --> 12:25.220
-Hey.
-Hey, Jackie.

12:31.804 --> 12:33.929
DeCourcy Ward.

12:33.929 --> 12:36.470
Jackie Rohr, FBI.
You mind if I call you D?

12:36.470 --> 12:39.387
Uh...no.
I have an arraignment.

12:39.387 --> 12:41.261
The arraignment's what I want
to talk to you about.

12:41.261 --> 12:43.053
You got a kid, Roach,
on your docket.

12:43.053 --> 12:45.095
He's an informant of mine.
He's working a decent case.

12:45.095 --> 12:47.136
He also shot a cop.

12:47.136 --> 12:49.470
Well, he allegedly
shot a cop.

12:51.303 --> 12:54.637
You want me to let him off?
Why me?

12:54.637 --> 12:56.470
Call it a professional favor.

12:56.470 --> 12:58.303
No, but why me...

12:58.303 --> 12:59.553
specifically?

12:59.553 --> 13:00.845
It's your case,
isn't it?

13:00.845 --> 13:02.637
[scoffs]

13:02.637 --> 13:04.804
Is there
a misunderstanding here?

13:04.804 --> 13:07.637
No, no, see,
I understand perfectly.

13:07.637 --> 13:09.261
You walk in here
and you think,

13:09.261 --> 13:11.720
oh, the new guy's stupid enough
to eat your bullshit.

13:11.720 --> 13:14.178
What are you,
some kind of asshole?

13:14.178 --> 13:16.970
I spent five years
with the U.S. Attorney,

13:16.970 --> 13:20.136
watching Feds cut deals
for pieces of shit like this.

13:20.136 --> 13:22.345
Take it to Guy Dan.
See what he says.

13:22.345 --> 13:25.178
Oh, well, excuse me,
Clarence Thomas.

13:25.178 --> 13:27.553
I'm sorry I gave you
the benefit of the doubt.

13:27.553 --> 13:29.345
I figured you weren't
Guy Dan's Uncle Tom,

13:29.345 --> 13:30.387
but clearly
I was mistaken.

13:30.387 --> 13:31.679
Don't worry.

13:32.970 --> 13:36.345
Next time, I won't ask.

13:37.679 --> 13:39.345
Oh, is that a threat?

13:39.345 --> 13:40.970
Threat?

13:40.970 --> 13:42.512
No.

13:42.512 --> 13:43.845
It's a "fuck you."

13:55.637 --> 14:00.011
[guard groaning]

14:01.261 --> 14:02.512
Aah!

14:02.512 --> 14:04.887
[all shouting and grunting]

14:04.887 --> 14:07.095
Hey!

14:07.095 --> 14:09.220
Hey!

14:09.220 --> 14:11.553
What the hell's fuckin'
goin' on back there?

14:11.553 --> 14:14.178
[gunshot]

14:14.178 --> 14:15.720
[tires squeal]

14:22.720 --> 14:24.303
[car horn honks]

14:30.261 --> 14:31.470
[man groaning]

14:33.929 --> 14:35.679
He saw my fucking face!

14:35.679 --> 14:36.929
What the fuck?

14:36.929 --> 14:38.804
He saw my fucking face!

14:55.762 --> 14:57.762
What the fuck are we gonna do?

14:57.762 --> 14:59.428
They saw my fucking face!

14:59.428 --> 15:01.053
Calm down.
You understand me?

15:01.053 --> 15:03.053
I don't know, man.
Let's just take their IDs,

15:03.053 --> 15:04.637
drop them off at the yard.

15:04.637 --> 15:06.345
What are you,
a fucking moron?

15:06.345 --> 15:07.804
We'll know where
their families live.

15:07.804 --> 15:09.428
I ain't hurting
someone's kids!

15:09.428 --> 15:11.804
Jesus, my kid's got
nothing to do with this.

15:11.804 --> 15:13.095
We're not gonna hurt
your goddamn kids.

15:13.095 --> 15:14.804
I'm not gonna say nothin'!

15:14.804 --> 15:17.095
-I don't know you.
-We won't say nothing.

15:17.095 --> 15:18.512
I don't know you either!

15:18.512 --> 15:19.929
Fuck!

15:21.470 --> 15:22.929
[breathing heavily]

15:26.095 --> 15:28.095
[guard] Look, I'm from
D Street in South--

15:28.095 --> 15:29.762
Nobody cares
where you're from!

15:29.762 --> 15:32.220
All's I'm saying
is I grew up with it.

15:32.220 --> 15:34.303
I'm not gonna rat
anyone out, on my life.

15:34.303 --> 15:37.136
If you were me,
would you trust you?

15:37.136 --> 15:39.762
[guard]
We'll take money, some of it.

15:39.762 --> 15:42.261
You get caught,
say we're in on it.

15:45.303 --> 15:47.220
That's not a bad idea.

15:47.220 --> 15:48.762
They saw my face.

15:48.762 --> 15:51.470
You want to worry about this
the rest of your life?

15:51.470 --> 15:53.220
It's on you.

15:53.220 --> 15:55.595
It's up to you, boss.

16:03.470 --> 16:08.053
[breathing heavily]

16:38.178 --> 16:39.512
I get one smoke?

17:10.428 --> 17:12.720
[guard]
Oh, my God!

17:12.720 --> 17:14.178
[guard sobbing]

17:18.512 --> 17:19.720
Oh, no.

17:20.887 --> 17:23.804
[guard screams]

17:23.804 --> 17:26.720
[Jackie panting]

17:30.261 --> 17:32.387
Wait, wait.
Hang on, hang on.

17:33.929 --> 17:35.428
[grunts]

17:35.428 --> 17:37.512
Okay, don't stop.
Don't stop.

17:37.512 --> 17:38.679
[laughs]

17:38.679 --> 17:40.095
Here, here. Ready?

17:41.345 --> 17:42.720
[both sigh]

17:44.095 --> 17:46.887
-[pots clang]
-Shh.

17:46.887 --> 17:50.345
[woman speaking Cantonese]

17:50.345 --> 17:52.887
What the fuck is she
ching-chonging about?

17:52.887 --> 17:54.095
She's calling you "gweilo."

17:54.095 --> 17:56.261
Gweilo? What the fuck
does that mean?

17:56.261 --> 17:58.303
Approximately,
"white devil."

17:58.303 --> 18:00.261
Ooh, she ain't wrong
about that.

18:00.261 --> 18:01.095
[both laugh]

18:07.387 --> 18:08.887
Come here, baby.

18:08.887 --> 18:10.720
[woman shouting in Cantonese]

18:10.720 --> 18:12.261
Ooh, gotta go.

18:12.261 --> 18:14.220
-[woman shouting]
