52:38.720 --> 52:40.512
This is DeCourcy Ward.

52:40.512 --> 52:42.637
This is the next
mayor of Boston.

52:42.637 --> 52:44.637
[man]
That'll be the day.

52:44.637 --> 52:45.845
[ice clinking]

52:45.845 --> 52:47.178
[Jackie]
Thanks for the drink.

52:49.220 --> 52:50.762
Who's that,
your priest?

52:50.762 --> 52:53.512
Yeah. Yeah, he cleans up
real good come Sunday.

52:53.512 --> 52:55.011
What can I do for you, D?

52:55.011 --> 52:57.011
You know,
you were right.

52:57.011 --> 52:58.679
We got off
on the left foot.

52:58.679 --> 53:01.428
What I should have done,
I realize now,

53:01.428 --> 53:04.970
is ask for a quid pro quo.

53:04.970 --> 53:06.720
What do you want?

53:06.720 --> 53:08.679
My way, which I got.

53:08.679 --> 53:09.929
[laughs]

53:09.929 --> 53:12.595
No, but, I mean, long-term.

53:12.595 --> 53:14.261
Honestly?

53:14.261 --> 53:17.011
I want to sail eight years
to my pension,

53:17.011 --> 53:20.220
get a job in
private security somewhere,

53:20.220 --> 53:22.679
never do another
honest day's work in my life.

53:22.679 --> 53:24.178
Okay.

53:24.178 --> 53:27.178
Well, look,
there's this case, right?

53:27.178 --> 53:29.345
Now, a case like this,
you can coast on,

53:29.345 --> 53:31.679
just like you coasted
on Angiulo in '83.

53:31.679 --> 53:33.220
[ice rattles]

53:33.220 --> 53:34.804
A couple days ago,

53:34.804 --> 53:37.220
a crew knocked over
an armored car in Revere.

53:38.220 --> 53:40.637
And the guards? Still missing.

53:42.512 --> 53:44.261
You're friends with
the federal prosecutor.

53:44.261 --> 53:45.929
What the fuck
do you need me for?

53:45.929 --> 53:48.845
I don't want this investigation
taken from me.

53:48.845 --> 53:50.387
I want to run it.

53:50.387 --> 53:52.428
And I don't want to just bury
who did it.

53:52.428 --> 53:54.595
No, I want to go
into Charlestown

53:54.595 --> 53:56.929
and I want to fuck
that place up.

53:57.887 --> 53:59.095
What about your boss?

53:59.095 --> 54:00.053
Fuck him.

54:00.053 --> 54:01.345
Fuck all of 'em.

54:01.345 --> 54:03.428
Fuck anyone else
who gets in my way.

54:06.095 --> 54:07.720
Mac.

54:07.720 --> 54:09.929
Can I get a whisky, neat?

54:09.929 --> 54:11.929
No, you see, this is good.

54:11.929 --> 54:13.679
This means you're learning.

54:16.553 --> 54:17.720
Stop.

54:22.887 --> 54:25.136
You do one.

54:25.136 --> 54:27.178
One.

54:27.178 --> 54:28.387
Whatever the takes are,
you're gettin'--

54:28.387 --> 54:29.637
Out.

54:29.637 --> 54:31.261
I don't want to hear
about the next one

54:31.261 --> 54:32.804
or some other fucking score
you got lined up.

54:32.804 --> 54:35.053
You take the money,
get straight.

54:35.053 --> 54:36.887
You understand?

54:36.887 --> 54:38.804
Uh-huh.

54:38.804 --> 54:40.136
What are you smiling at?

54:41.220 --> 54:43.512
You love it too much,
don't you?

54:43.512 --> 54:46.303
Didn't take much,
getting you to do it again.

54:46.303 --> 54:48.387
Took almost nothing.

54:48.387 --> 54:50.136
Yeah.

54:50.136 --> 54:51.345
[sniffles]

54:51.345 --> 54:53.303
-Jimmy, keep your fucking--
-Hello.

54:57.595 --> 54:58.387
[Minogue]
Frank.

55:02.220 --> 55:03.553
I wanna do another one.

55:03.553 --> 55:05.929
Another truck.

55:05.929 --> 55:07.470
After last time?

55:10.428 --> 55:12.679
You guys allergic to money
all of a sudden?

55:12.679 --> 55:15.345
But I'm not gonna work
with this guy, Frankie.

55:15.345 --> 55:16.887
What am I? What?
What am I, dog shit?

55:16.887 --> 55:18.345
-[laughs]
-Hey, shh.

55:18.345 --> 55:20.053
No, you're a fucking
wasted sperm cell.

55:20.053 --> 55:21.804
I'm a wasted fuckin' sp--
That's a good one.

55:21.804 --> 55:23.345
-Shut your fuckin' mouth.
-Know what? I've been robbin'

55:23.345 --> 55:24.136
since I was
eight years fuckin' old.

55:24.136 --> 55:25.220
What have you been doing, Tommy?

55:25.220 --> 55:26.929
And you've been getting caught.

55:26.929 --> 55:27.804
I been gettin' caught?
Hey, fuck you! Fuck you!

55:27.804 --> 55:29.095
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

55:29.095 --> 55:31.136
-[Frankie] Hey! Hey!
-Fuck you!

55:31.136 --> 55:33.345
-[Frankie] Shut the fuck up!
-[Tommy] Punk!

55:33.345 --> 55:34.804
Fuck me? I'll break
your fucking neck!

55:34.804 --> 55:36.095
Hey!

55:36.095 --> 55:37.970
-[others shushing]
-Come and get me, punk.

55:37.970 --> 55:39.720
-Hey, relax--
-Come and get me!

55:39.720 --> 55:41.470
-Get in the fuckin' car.
-[Jimmy] I'm goin'!

55:41.470 --> 55:43.679
-[Frankie] Get in the car.
-[Tommy] Frankie!

55:43.679 --> 55:45.512
-Frankie!
-I'm goin' again.

55:45.512 --> 55:47.345
I'd love to have you join me.

55:47.345 --> 55:48.887
Let me know if you can do it,
all right?

55:48.887 --> 55:51.387
[Tommy] Frank! You know
what you're doin'?

55:52.804 --> 55:54.053
Get the fuck out of the rain.

55:54.053 --> 55:55.512
This is fucking stupid.

55:55.512 --> 55:57.762
[Frankie] Turn your
fucking head around.

55:57.762 --> 56:00.011
See? It's not that complicated
what we're trying to do here.

56:00.011 --> 56:01.970
It's just a matter of how far
you're willing to go,

56:01.970 --> 56:04.178
how much shit
you're willing to eat.

56:04.178 --> 56:05.553
I can do what I got to do.

56:07.220 --> 56:08.512
Okay.

56:08.512 --> 56:09.470
So...

56:11.053 --> 56:12.595
we know that
our perpetrators

56:12.595 --> 56:16.136
are most likely a few pieces
of shit from Charlestown, right?

56:16.136 --> 56:17.762
There's more bank robbers
in Charlestown

56:17.762 --> 56:20.637
than any other square mile
in the English-speaking world.

56:20.637 --> 56:24.387
But you can't convict them,
because they don't talk.

56:24.387 --> 56:27.595
So, we use
what you've got.

56:27.595 --> 56:29.387
You're the DA.

56:29.387 --> 56:31.303
You got the number-one thing
that's going to scare

56:31.303 --> 56:34.303
every piece of shit
in this city.

56:34.303 --> 56:35.804
The grand jury.

56:35.804 --> 56:39.804
No scumbag can work
when the grand jury is on.

56:39.804 --> 56:41.762
So, what we do

56:41.762 --> 56:44.595
is we find a big case
gone cold.

56:44.595 --> 56:47.804
We round up every bank-robbing
suspect we can,

56:47.804 --> 56:51.136
and you grant them immunity
on the cold case.

56:51.136 --> 56:53.595
Then, when you get them
in front of the grand jury,

56:53.595 --> 56:56.095
you hit them with questions
about the robbery.

56:56.095 --> 56:58.136
It's jail time,
they don't want to talk to you.

56:58.136 --> 56:59.762
How'd you figure all that?

56:59.762 --> 57:03.595
D.C. law school.
Class of '68, motherfucker.

57:07.011 --> 57:08.428
It's a risky move.

57:10.053 --> 57:12.679
But given the circumstances:

57:12.679 --> 57:14.637
three dead bodies,

57:14.637 --> 57:17.095
Charlestown, black DA.

57:17.095 --> 57:19.303
People will probably
give you credit.

57:29.970 --> 57:31.261
[door opens]

58:03.261 --> 58:06.595
So I gotta ask you,
what changed your mind?

58:07.845 --> 58:10.345
About you?

58:10.345 --> 58:11.970
Beyond necessity?

58:16.261 --> 58:17.679
You'd said something.

58:17.679 --> 58:19.679
Reminded me
when I was a kid.

58:21.595 --> 58:26.178
My father,
he worked for the SCLC.

58:26.178 --> 58:27.845
He knew King.

58:27.845 --> 58:30.303
He was in Memphis
when King was shot.

58:32.887 --> 58:35.261
And when I was a kid,

58:35.261 --> 58:37.845
he'd come home
getting his head kicked in

58:37.845 --> 58:39.804
by the Bull Connors
of the world...

58:42.637 --> 58:45.011
and he'd beat the living shit
out of us.

58:47.970 --> 58:49.136
He, uh...

58:50.553 --> 58:51.720
[sighs]

58:53.970 --> 58:56.470
...caught me with a thumb
one night.

58:59.970 --> 59:01.970
You're right.

59:01.970 --> 59:04.553
Only the bad understand.

59:08.637 --> 59:10.387
Irony abounds.

59:19.470 --> 59:23.637
♪ So many people
Have come and gone ♪

59:23.637 --> 59:27.261
♪ Their faces fade
As the years go by ♪

59:27.261 --> 59:28.428
[rapid, deep breaths]

59:28.428 --> 59:30.053
♪ Yet I still recall... ♪

59:30.053 --> 59:31.762
Go, go!

59:31.762 --> 59:35.303
Drop the fucking bag,
motherfucker!

59:35.303 --> 59:37.512
Down! Down!
Get the fuck down!

59:50.595 --> 59:52.804
♪ It's more than a feeling ♪

59:52.804 --> 59:54.720
♪ More than a feeling ♪

59:54.720 --> 59:57.220
♪ When I hear that old song
They used to play ♪

59:57.220 --> 59:59.387
♪ More than a feeling ♪

59:59.387 --> 1:00:01.387
♪ And I begin dreaming ♪

1:00:01.387 --> 1:00:02.970
♪ More than a feeling ♪

1:00:02.970 --> 1:00:06.136
♪ Till I see Marianne
Walk away ♪

1:00:06.136 --> 1:00:08.637
I'm going to be a lot more
valuable to you now.

1:00:09.970 --> 1:00:11.428
That robbery up at Revere?

1:00:13.011 --> 1:00:14.887
I know where the bodies
are buried.

1:00:16.303 --> 1:00:18.136
♪

1:00:55.136 --> 1:00:59.345
♪ When I'm tired
and thinking cold ♪

1:00:59.345 --> 1:01:03.804
♪ I hide in my music,
forget the day ♪

1:01:03.804 --> 1:01:04.804
♪ And dream of a girl
I used to know ♪
